node.text:
Whether you were aware or not, @nickyjam magically got everyone to stand up and dance the entire time during his performance.

What a night watching nearly 10,000 people during the pandemic celebrate and actually have some fun.

If there’s anything America and the world needs today is a bit of value, entertainment and a ton of laughter.

All three were brought during awards ceremony night.
Future looks bright!

node.title: Nicky Jam brought the house down at MGM Grand Arena

node.title: Ever wonder why money always flows to millionaires & billionaires?

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Patrick Bet-David in Fort Lauderdale, Florida. May be an image of 1 person and text that says 'Patrick Bet-David @patrickbetdavid People always underestimate the sacrifices required to be great. Even more if you want to be the greatest in your industry.'.

node.text:
READ CAPTION BELOW!

The choice for greatness will always be yours.

Many of the sacrifices made behind closed doors won’t ever be seen.

There’s no camera following you around to highlight the real tough choices being made.

Some of them won’t even make sense to you at times.

The people I related to anytime I had others try second guessing my decisions were soldiers on the front lines. They put it all on the line and miss out so much.

Athletes who are on a run for greatness.  The Brady’s of the world. The Kobe’s. The Federer’s. The Steve Jobs. The Sam Walton.

Those who ran for office and won. The next handshake. The next town hall meeting. The 1,000th person asking you the same question you’ve answered a thousand times. The number of speeches given in a daily basis.  The number of negative articles written about you that try to mentally destroy you.

I guess what I’m saying is that there are levels to the game.

There are the critics
The fans
The man in the arena
Then the man who wins in the arena
Then the one who continuous to win even after everyone else always considers him the best.

You get to choose which level you want to be in life.

Make sure the effort and sacrifices matches the level you want to reach.

Goodnight!

node.text:
Back in 2002 we were at a Christmas party.  One of our relatives casually disrespected my Dad.

I told my Dad we’re leaving the party.  My Dad was upset and embarrassed of me wanting to leave early.

I was furious that a relative whom my Dad helped when he was younger in Iran would have the audacity to speak to my Dad in that manner.

When we got in the car, I looked at my Dad and told him the following.

“Dad, these people will eat their words one day. I PROMISE YOU I will work so hard everyday until the world knows your last name.  They’re gonna have to kill me to stop me from making that a reality. I PROMISE YOU.”

Here was the problem.

In 2002, I was broke with nothing to my name. I was $49,000 in debt.  No one knew me. I was about to go back in the Army because nothing was going my way.

The rest is history.

My Dad has and always will be my #1 hero.  This man changed my life.

That smile in the picture is worth everything.

PS:  just getting warmed up. Future looks bright!
